@scenario_hash:83f3eb8000cbd2dc
Scenario: a standard library parser can read the manifest without custom code
  Given the manifest file is present at its well-known path
  When a script imports only a standard format parsing library (no custom manifest module)
  And the script reads the manifest file using that library
  Then the script can extract the canonical name of every declared BC
  without raising a parse error or requiring manual string manipulation

@scenario_hash:d36837de225d188c
Scenario: the manifest format requires no documentation to parse
  Given the manifest file is present at its well-known path
  When a developer reads the manifest file directly
  Then each manifest entry contains only the expected field names and no others

@scenario_hash:d035f5ca9d69bb4d
Scenario: a pipeline script can extract all GitHub remote URLs from the manifest
  Given the manifest file contains entries for all six product BCs
  When a shell or Python script reads the manifest file and extracts all GitHub remote URLs
  Then the script produces exactly six URLs, one per declared BC
  And each URL is the full GitHub remote URL for that BC's repository
